Subject: Re: [T2] how do I tell if I have hydraulic lifters?

On Friday, April 09, 2004, at 03:18PM, Jay Ollom <jaytype2(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

>Yes, I know there is a description in the library but I guess I'm just a guy 
>who really has to see it to believe it.  Does anybody our there have 
>pictures that show the difference between a hydraulic and a solid lifter?

Solid lifters have almost no waist and are well, solid:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Damage/lifterwear.jpg

The hydraulic lifter will have a more noticeable one along with an oiling hole in the side and a snap ring on one end to keep the piston inside the lifter. There's a picture in Bentley...

